node.text: This one-pan dinner brings together chickpeas, marinara sauce, and mozzarella in a single skillet, then tops it off with wedges of roasted broccoli florets. A crunchy Parmesan-and-panko blend is the final touch to this comforting, easy, and nutritious meal. Get the recipe featured in our October issue at the link in bio! 📷: @johnny_miller_  recipe by:  @sarahcarey1  food styling by:  @mpearljones  prop styling by:  @suzie_myers

node.text: @MarthaStewartKitchen is coming soon to a store near you! From appetizers and sides, to entrees and desserts, find some of @marthastewart48's most popular and favorite recipes at your local store. Learn more at the link in bio! 👆🏼

node.text: While there are certain long-time meccas for craft-beer innovation—such as Michigan, Colorado, Northern California, and Wisconsin—new markets have emerged across the country, many in quaint smaller towns and in restored buildings like former fire stations, churches, or other historic structures. From a beer farm in Southern Illinois that forages for infused ingredients on its property and rims a national forest to a brewery-to-table taproom or restaurant in Maui where beers are inspired by locally grown tropical fruits, we round up 10 brewery taprooms to visit across the U.S at the link in bio. Plus, leave a comment below with your favorites! 📷: @drinkcsb

node.text: It's the one-year anniversary of Martha Stewart CBD!  After one year of combining gourmet flavors with state-of-the-art CBD isolate, Martha's line of gummies, oils, and pet treats continues to grow. Follow @marthastewartcbd for giveaways to celebrate one year of calm, and shop Martha’s CBD products at the link in bio.

node.text: Unlock a worn wooden bookcase's star-is-born potential with a fresh coat of paint. Painting the exterior of your bookcase in one hue where these types of items are displayed and the interior another color will completely transform the way you see your favorite novelties. Get our tutorial at the link in bio! 📷: @addiejuell

node.text: After a long day at school, kids cannot wait to unwind and enjoy an afternoon snack. Here, we've given kid-friendly cereal treats an upgrade with four flavorful variations. Learn how to make the basic recipe, then try our riffs like freeze-dried raspberries and white chocolate, or cocktail peanuts and semisweet chocolate. Get the recipes at the link in bio. 📷: @kirstenrfrancis recipe by: @flossylucille

node.text: Over the past decade, @marthastewart48 has planted hundreds of Japanese maples on her farm in Bedford—and every autumn, the still-diminutive trees put on a dazzling show. "I first became enamored with Japanese maples when I visited Japan with my then-husband and daughter years ago. On our travels from city to countryside, we saw many types of this graceful tree. It was autumn, and their colors ranged from brilliant reds to bright oranges to yellow-golds, and even the darkest magentas. I was entranced. I vowed that I would plant as many as I could, in as many different sizes, forms, and colors as possible," writes Martha in our October issue. Feast your eyes on their brilliant foliage, and learn how she helps them thrive in our October issue out on newsstands or at the link in bio. 📷: @minh_ngoc

node.text: If you're intrigued by the speckled borlotti beans at the farmers' market, this minestrone is the perfect excuse to grab a few pounds. The hearty soup is flexible by nature—think of the ingredients as mere suggestions. Didn't find borlottis? Use butter beans instead, or canned versions of either. No escarole or kale in sight? Toss in another leafy green—say, mustard greens or chard. Last, stir in cooked pasta; any shape you can eat with a spoon will do! Get the recipe at the link in bio! 📷: @pissinginthepunchbowl recipe by: @lucullanfoods food styling by: @rebeccajurkevich prop styling by: @tanyagraff1
